{"id": "EUVD-2025-20069", "enisaUuid": "ba65fb0f-90ed-3c34-bf56-e6170875c415", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/nouveau: fix a use-after-free in r535_gsp_rpc_push()\n\nThe RPC container is released after being passed to r535_gsp_rpc_send().\n\nWhen sending the initial fragment of a large RPC and passing the\ncaller's RPC container, the container will be freed prematurely. Subsequent\nattempts to send remaining fragments will therefore result in a\nuse-after-free.\n\nAllocate a temporary RPC container for holding the initial fragment of a\nlarge RPC when sending. Free the caller's container when all fragments\nare successfully sent.\n\n[ Rebase onto Blackwell changes. - Danilo ]", "datePublished": "2025-07-04T15:31:08", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-19T21:31:14", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/cd4677407c0ee250fc21e36439c8a442ddd62cc1", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9802f0a63b641f4cddb2139c814c2e95cb825099", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38187"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38187"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "13207395-2171-3490-8d5e-f9780d703e45", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "1f9f906f-5ff1-3b0e-80be-dfb5d4394607", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.7"}, {"id": "43e5a75a-9e1f-343f-a65a-c85e3229f70d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "176fdcbddfd288408ce8571c1760ad618d962096 <9802f0a63b641f4cddb2139c814c2e95cb825099"}, {"id": "4dab78f1-e2f9-3c9c-81ec-50d6811c3425", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15.4"}, {"id": "6e5a7a12-c2f1-3c34-899c-e6c495ff3610", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "176fdcbddfd288408ce8571c1760ad618d962096 <cd4677407c0ee250fc21e36439c8a442ddd62cc1"}, {"id": "bb4b07e3-8a0e-389e-8fc6-06c54b28f9b1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16"}, {"id": "e593faeb-0180-3873-be32-b83e4d7a9600", "